---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout title="Install BridgeAIChat Agent" description="Install and configure a BridgeAIChat agent on a remote device.">
  <section class="surface">
    <div class="eyebrow">Install</div>
    <h1>Turn a machine into a BridgeAIChat agent.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Each agent device keeps its own AI CLI, working directory, and runtime context. The current installer can stay
      minimal: it creates <code>agent.yaml</code>, auto-derives identity, and optionally installs a startup service.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid two">
    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">Release</div>
      <h2>Use the agent archive</h2>
      <pre>tar -xzf bridge-agent_v0.1.0-beta.1_darwin_arm64.tar.gz
cd bridge-agent_v0.1.0-beta.1_darwin_arm64
export BRIDGE_AGENT_GATEWAY_URL=ws://your-control-host:8080/agent
bash install-agent.sh</pre>
      <p>This writes <code>agent.yaml</code> beside the release files and can also register the agent as a background service.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">Run</div>
      <h2>Start the agent</h2>
      <pre>./bridge-agent -config ./agent.yaml</pre>
      <p>Once the websocket connects, the matching device should switch from <code>Agent Missing</code> to <code>Connected</code> in the UI.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid two">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Requirements</div>
      <h2>What must exist on the device</h2>
      <ul class="list tight">
        <li><code>tmux</code> for Codex and other tmux-backed tools</li>
        <li>Tailscale connectivity to the control host</li>
        <li>An AI CLI already installed locally, such as Codex, Claude, or OpenClaw</li>
        <li>A reachable websocket URL for the gateway, usually a Tailscale IP or MagicDNS hostname</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="muted" style="margin-top:14px">The built-in <code>Bridge Helper</code> is always available once the agent connects, even though it does not appear in <code>agent.yaml</code>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">Example</div>
      <h2>Minimal Claude config</h2>
      <pre>default_tool: claude

tools:
  claude:
    cmd: claude
    args: ["-p", "--dangerously-skip-permissions"]
    continue_args: ["--continue", "-p", "--dangerously-skip-permissions"]
    direct: true

gateway:
  url: ws://100.101.102.103:8080/agent</pre>
      <p><code>direct: true</code> is required for Claude. <code>--dangerously-skip-permissions</code> prevents Claude from blocking on interactive prompts that have no stdin to answer them.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
